Get Started

- Save programs with the .py extension (for example hello.py).
- Run from a terminal: python hello.py (or py hello.py on some Windows setups).
- Check version: python --version
- In the interactive REPL, exit with exit() or quit(), or Ctrl+Z then Enter (Windows) / Ctrl+D (macOS/Linux).

First program: print("Hello, World!")

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_getstarted.asp

Next folder: 0.3_Syntax
